# Pass-2 blocking finding (single, from feature-coverage)
blockingFindings[1]{id,severity,description,fix}:
  HF-04,blocking,"Four doctor error codes missing from section 7 error catalog (DOCTOR_HOOK_TIMEOUT, DOCTOR_PERMISSIONS_MISMATCH, DOCTOR_VERSION_SKEW, DOCTOR_UPDATE_AVAILABLE). Live production failure modes fall through to exit code 2 (internal error), making CI gating unreliable. Originally raised pass-1 as high; not applied in integrator pass; now blocking on convergence loop.",Add 4 rows to section 7 error table with severity + exit code + remediation columns

# High-priority items raised pass-1, still open after integrator
highFindings[2]{id,severity,description,fix}:
  HF-05,high,"Tier passthrough audit incomplete. Phase 3 covers loom-init, loom-auto, loom-roadmap/init but loom-quick, loom-change, loom-plan also trigger registration paths and bypass the --tier flag.",Extend Phase 3 deliverables + section 9 ownership matrix with the 3 missing command files; add Phase 3 acceptance criterion covering all entry-point commands
  HF-10,high,"Differentiation gap. Section 1 Vision describes mechanics but omits explicit differentiator (loom-doctor TOON output composing with /loom-converge vs GSD/cc-plugins).",Add one sentence to section 1 Vision: 'Unlike generic Claude Code plugins, Loom ships /loom-doctor whose TOON output pipes directly into /loom-converge — the install health check is a first-class convergence signal, not a diagnostic sidebar.' Also add to Phase 4a README acceptance criteria.

